# Root env (Vite SPA)
#
# This SPA stores API settings in browser local storage (Settings modal),
# so you usually don't need any env vars here.
#
# Keep this file for operator convenience and future toggles.

# Vite dev server port (optional)
# VITE_PORT=5173

# Optional default gateway base URL for your own tooling/scripts.
# (The app itself reads gateway URL from Settings storage, not env.)
# GENAI_STUDIO_GATEWAY_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8080

# GenAI Studio SPA (Vite). Copy to `.env` (or `.env.local`) in the repo root.
# When `VITE_GATEWAY_URL` is set, the app defaults to the hosted **Express** gateway
# (see `deploy/README.md` — e.g. `docker compose -f deploy/docker-compose.yml up`).
# VITE_GATEWAY_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8080
# Optional: VITE_USE_GATEWAY=true  (if omitted, a set VITE_GATEWAY_URL implies enabled)
#
# Dev + gateway proxy: browse at http://localhost:5173 — fetches use `/__vite_gateway`; Vite forwards to
# `DEV_GATEWAY_PROXY_TARGET` (fallback: `VITE_GATEWAY_URL`, then http://127.0.0.1:8080).
# Prefer local Express when `docker compose … up` exposes the gateway on 8080 (avoids flaky tunnels):
# VITE_DEV_GATEWAY_PROXY=true
# DEV_GATEWAY_PROXY_TARGET=http://127.0.0.1:8080
# Dev proxy uses a streaming-safe Node pipe (not http-proxy) so `/v1/intelligent/chat` SSE and memory routes avoid spurious 502s.
# HTTPS tunnel with a self-signed edge: DEV_GATEWAY_PROXY_TLS_INSECURE=true (dev only).
# If GET /__vite_gateway/... returns 401, set this to the same value as `GATEWAY_BEARER_TOKEN` in `deploy/.env`
# (overrides the browser `Authorization` header for the dev proxy only):
# DEV_GATEWAY_PROXY_AUTH_TOKEN=your-gateway-bearer
# If the gateway is only behind Cloudflare Tunnel, use HTTPS (you may see HTTP 530 when the tunnel is down):
# DEV_GATEWAY_PROXY_TARGET=https://your-gateway.example.com
